## Phase 2, stabilize Google layout load ownership

### Goal

Make `GoogleLayout` load only when it should, and only once per project switch.

### Why this comes early

The current and recent logs show the layout has historically performed unnecessary loads:

* startup load while no project exists
* repeated loads around `set_project(None -> 1)`
* post-create refresh churn

Even in the clean baseline, this is the first technical debt that should be removed before UX layering continues. 

### Scope

Only in `GoogleLayout`:

* suppress no-project loads
* make `set_project()` the owner of project-bound loading
* remove duplicate pre-load and post-create load patterns
* add a simple reload gate or debounce
* do not touch `GoogleLayoutLegacy`

### Acceptance criteria

* no “No project selected” load before a real project is set
* one clean load after project creation or project switch
* no generation storms during project creation
* photo grid remains stable

### Deliverable

A technically quieter `GoogleLayout` that is safe to improve visually later.

